    "body": "It looks like this feature probably needs to be added to the [WebChromeClient](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/webkit/WebChromeClient.html), which is part of the [React Native Webview Bridge](https://github.com/alinz/react-native-webview-bridge) module. \r\n\r\nHowever, [React Native Webview Bridge](https://github.com/alinz/react-native-webview-bridge) has not accepted a PR in over a year, so I am not sure if that is the best direction. \r\n\r\nThe other option would be to migrate to [react-native webviews](https://github.com/facebook/react-native/blob/master/ReactAndroid/src/main/java/com/facebook/react/views/webview/ReactWebViewManager.java#L360) and open a PR to get more permission handling on the WebView there. \r\n\r\nI am not sure if `status` uses the `RPC` functionality that the `Webview Bridge` provides?\r\nThoughts?",
